South Africa-based platinum group metals (PGM) miner Southern Palladium has been granted a secondary listing on the main board of the JSE, subject to the primary listing of shares on the ASX. The company was admitted to the official list of ASX on June 6. Accordingly, Southern Palladium’s shares will start trading on the ASX and the JSE on June 8. Southern Palladium’s PGM advanced stage exploration project Bengwenyama, in Limpopo, has an estimated resource of 18.8-million ounces of platinum, palladium, rhodium and gold.